description:
Job Highlights

Fun, young, and joyful working environment
Create ideas & improve designs for Manner Group
Coordinate with art and creative team

Responsibilities:

Copywriting or creating content and script for social media platforms
Handle production and sales project and creative, pre-production, on location shooting and post-production;
Work with Director and Production team to make sure project on time and within budget;
Time management, able to meet tight deadlines and work independently under pressure in fast paced environment;
Keep the team in a good production atmosphere
Requirements:

Three to five years of the production company or producer experience is preferred;
Able to plan independently, to coordinate, organize, and screen projects, and be familiar with the program production process;
Work experience in online marketing, social media group will be preferred;
Knowledge of production software; after Effects, Photoshop and Illustrator etc.;
Have a passion for the Internet or film industry, with enthusiasm, initiative, team awareness and coordination and strong resistance;
Work with Production Team

職位要求:

至少三至五年以上製作公司創作經驗; 獨立統籌，創作影片包括前中後期製作；篩選項目; 熟悉製作流程，有豐富影視製作，凝聚團隊，有應變能力處理突發危機，協作劇本和拍攝要求策劃拍攝.

To apply, please send us your resume / CV to us. Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes only.

Responsibilities:

Design high quality television broadcast video graphics for news;
Working on On-Air Promo graphics;
Create and implement design concepts with 2D & 3D computer software;
Work closely with the creative team in design & production.

Requirements:

At least 3-year experience in broadcast design or graphic design;
Proficient with all major Adobe software (Photoshop, Illustrator & After Effects) and 3D software (Cinema4D);
Innovative with excellent conceptual creativity;
Able to work independently under tight deadlines;
Proficiency in Putonghua is an advantage;
Strong 3D skill is an advantage;
Knowledge of Unreal Engine is an advantage;
Less experience will be considered as graphic designer.



For more details of our company, please visit our website at http://www.ifeng.com/

We offer attractive remuneration package to the right candidate. Interested parties please send applications with detailed resume stating career history, present & expected salary and date available to Human Resources Department, Phoenix Satellite Television Co. Ltd. via e-mail: phxhr@ phoenixtv.com or via fax: 2200 8620.

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.  Applicants not hearing from us within 6 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and all related information will be destroyed after 6 months.

Responsibilities: 

         Production of On-Air Promotions, Corporate Video and Sales tape. 

Requirements: 

Certificate/Diploma/Degree holder in Journalism / Communication, with 5 years relevant working experience;
Solid experience in directing shoots and proficiency in non-linear editing skill (e.g. Apple Final Cut Pro);
Creative with good knowledge of video graphic design;
Able to work independently under tight schedule;
Excellent command of written and spoken English and Chinese, proficiency in Putonghua is an advantage; and
Candidates with more experience will be considered for senior position. 

For more details of our company, please visit our website at http://www.ifeng.com/



We offer attractive remuneration package to the right candidate. Interested parties please send applications with detailed resume stating career history, present & expected salary and date available to Human Resources Department, Phoenix Satellite Television Co. Ltd. via fax: 2200 8620.

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.  Applicants not hearing from us within 6 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful and all related information will be destroyed after 6 months.

One Click Go Live Limited (“ONE CLICK GO LIVE”) is a live streaming technology company focuses on enterprise broadcast-grade video live streaming solutions with offerings including live streaming platforms, products and services. ONE CLICK GO LIVE enables corporates to conduct professional live streaming through one single button – ONE CLICK GO LIVE, delivering a seamless user experience in combination with patented technologies.

Serving over 300 corporates for over 9,000 live streaming events, ONE CLICK GO LIVE leverages its technical expertise while corporates focus on generating growth and revenue with video content. 

Our successful cases: www.oneclickgolive.com

We are looking for candidate(s) who is/are interested to join our fast growing team.  Training will be offered for potential candidate(s).


Job responsibility:

To install, maintain and support the IT infrastructure, security, networking, server computers and messaging systems;
Manage Internal IT systems (i.e. web, email, applications and server, etc.); 
Responsible for the installation, administration, maintenance, configuration and support the smooth running of the enterprise network;
Manage infrastructure projects in a quality and timely manner;
Manage system databases and servers to ensure smooth on-going operation and up-time according to service standards.  Plan and perform database version upgrades;
Perform regular network scanning, analysis and threat identification;
Manage and maintain documentation of all IT assets and ensure all processes & procedure are compliant with the company policies;
Manage service transition and release to production process to ensure network infrastructure setup and its components are complied with enterprise technical standard;
Design, deploy, and administer the network infrastructure and supporting systems;
To assist and provide support to solve end user's technical problems including but not limited to any hardware, software and network systems (Operating System, MS Office suite, antivirus, email- client, office printing system, networking, etc.) ;
Provide off-hours operational support for emergency maintenance and deployment events when necessary;

 Job requirement:

Diploma or Degree holders in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related discipline

At least 3-5 years' working experience in server administration and server networking or performing in system support role
Exposure in Live audio/video streaming support will be an advantage
Sound knowledge and technical skills and Microsoft Windows 
Solid experience in Windows Server platform, Active directory, Group Policy, VMare, Networking, Firewall, switch and router
Experience with MacOS will have an added advantage
Willing to provide ad hoc support in non-office hours, if required
Strong problem solving and good interpersonal skills
Interested applicants please send us full CV with current and expected salary and availability.

Benefits : Medical Allowance, Birthday and Childcare Leave 

The information provided will be treated in strict confidence and used only for consideration of application for relevant/similar post(s).  All personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within 6 months.
